Vice President Harris welcomed Prime Minister Johnson to the White House, highlighting the long-standing and enduring relationship between the US and the UK. They discussed shared priorities such as addressing global health, climate change, and upholding democratic principles. Prime Minister Johnson expressed gratitude for US cooperation, particularly during the Kabul airlift, and praised the US government's efforts in allowing vaccinated British citizens to travel to the US. He also mentioned progress in trade relations, including the removal of bans on British beef and tariffs on Scotch whiskey. Both leaders emphasized the importance of tackling climate change and standing up for democratic values.